The office of the DPP yesterday confirmed to a Mombasa court that it will not call witnesses in a case for US extradition of drugs trafficking suspects.Assistant DPP Alexander Muteti said he will instead use affidavits from the US.Baktash Akasha Abdalla, Ibrahim Akasha Abdalla, Gulam Hussein and Vijaygiri Anandgiri Goswami are wanted in the US for drug trafficking. They were arrested by anti-narcotics police officers at the Akashas home in Nyali. The court will give directions on December 9.